      "prompt": "What is occupational therapy?",
      "reply": "Occupational therapy is a healthcare profession that helps individuals overcome physical, cognitive, or emotional barriers to engage in meaningful activities, or occupations, that are important to them. Occupational therapists work with individuals of all ages to improve independence, develop or regain skills, and enhance overall quality of life."
