      "prompt": "What is the difference between physical therapy and occupational therapy?",
      "reply": "Physical therapy primarily focuses on the rehabilitation of physical impairments and movement dysfunction. It aims to restore mobility, reduce pain, and improve physical function. Occupational therapy, on the other hand, focuses on helping individuals participate in meaningful activities, such as self-care, work, and leisure, by addressing physical, cognitive, and emotional factors."
